A woman was yesterday killed by a buffalo at Lolldaiga Ranch in Umande. Esther Biwott, 61, was attacked by a buffalo when she went to fetch firewood in the ranch’s forest on Friday morning. Biwott’s son Martin Kipkemboi said he heard screams from the forest where his mother was in the company of about 30 women. “The officers from the ranch rushed to rescue her but she was seriously injured,“ said Kipkemboi. She was pronounced dead on arrival at Nanyuki Cottage Hospital. Avoid becoming a victim of Fake News. Subscribe to the Standard Group SMS service by texting 'NEWS' to 22840.